# File and Module Hygiene

- Use `.ts` for non-UI modules (config, API services, utilities, Redux logic) and `.tsx` only when JSX is present.
- Avoid duplicate or suffixed clones such as `file 2.tsx`; refactor the original module instead.
- Keep one primary responsibility per file; split large mixed-concern modules into focused units.
- Standardize naming in new code (`calendar` over misspelled variants) while preserving existing API contracts.
- Prefer explicit exports for shared modules to keep dependencies clear and tree-shake friendly.
